parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump flange can cause fuel to leak, potentially leading to a fire hazard, which can result in serious injury or loss of life.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the fuel pump flange
fuel spraying onto the rider's leg and motorcycle parts
fuel dripping onto the hot engine exhaust
fuel smell
gas gauge displaying incorrect fuel levels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel strip can cause the gas gauge to display incorrect fuel levels, leading to unexpected fuel depletion, which can strand the rider or cause accidents.
symptoms: Gas gauge showing incorrect fuel levels
fuel tank may be full or empty despite gas gauge reading
fuel strip not correctly displaying the amount of fuel in the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel final drive can cause the rear wheel to lock up and skid, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Oil leakage from the final drive
worn or damaged drive shaft
excessive oil leak from the rear wheel
rear brake pads damaged due to oil leakage
rear wheel moves side to side
difficulty downshifting
and unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking of the flange can cause the rear wheel to lock up and skid, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Cracked bolt holes in the flange
difficulty shifting gears
and unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the drive-line seal can cause oil leakage, leading to damage to the rear brake pads and other components.
symptoms: Oil leakage from the final drive
worn or damaged drive shaft
and excessive oil leak from the rear wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS pump can cause a complete loss of brakes, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brakes
brake lever feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
ABS and brake failure lights flashing
residual braking only.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of the rear brake pads can cause a loss of rear braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rear brake pads wear out prematurely
typically in 6
000 miles
loss of rear braking ability
rear brake rotor is very hot even when neither brake levers have been employed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty front brake switch can cause ABS brake failure, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: ABS brake failure
hard to stop the bike
near-miss with another vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel flange can cause the wheel to become loose or detached, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Cracks on the rear wheel flange
wheel looseness or detachment
unusual noises or vibrations while riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Quick Disconnect Fitting Failure

unusual noises or smells while riding.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of body panels can cause distractions, loss of control, or injuries to the rider or passengers.
